            <main>
                <h1>Site Plan</h1>
                <h2>Website Purpose</h2>
                <p>The purpose of the website Converts of London is to bring people together
                    by sharing their conversion stories. This site is specifically catered
                    to those converts who are currently living in London.</p>

                <h2>Audience</h2>
                <p>The audience for Converts of London would be a member of the LDS church,
                    specifically to those who reside in the United Kingdom, but not limited to
                    them. Anyone who is a member of the church could find joy through this site.
                    People who use this site would be aged 16 to 45. </p>

                <h2>Personas</h2>
                <h3>James Walker</h3>
                <p>James is a 25 year old man who has recently returned home from
                    serving a mission in Germany. He is originally from England, and after
                    serving a mission, he is interested to know about the missionary efforts
                    taking place in his home country. He would use this site to share these
                    stories with his friends or other investigators.</p>

                <h3>Leann Campbell</h3>
                <p>Leann Campbell is a 37 year old woman who has only heard negative things
                    about the LDS church. She has a few friends who are LDS, but she is always
                    to afraid to ask them about their religion. She would use this site to learn
                    about the LDS faith, and discover what kind of people belong to this church.
                    If she did decided to convert, she could also share her story here to positively
                    influence others.</p>

                <h2>Scenarios</h2>
                <ol>
                    <li>Users will be able to read about others' stories and experiences.</li>
                    <li>Users would be able to upload their own story and image.</li>
                    <li>Viewers can vote on stories they like.</li>
                    <li>Users can create, edit, and delete their own profile.</li>
                    <li>Contact the website with concerns or suggestions.</li>
                </ol>

                <h2>Asset List</h2>
                <ol>
                    <li>Login page where users can log in or create an account</li>
                    <li>Home page describing the website</li>
                    <li>About page with further description about the website</li>
                    <li>Gallery page where visitors can read and vote on shared stories</li>
                    <li>Share page where users can upload their own story and image</li>
                    <li>Contact page where users can use a form to contact administrators</li>
                </ol>
                
